68template<typename T, class Op, class Op8>
69void vBinOp8(const T* src1, size_t step1, const T* src2, size_t step2, T* dst, size_t step, Size sz)
70{
71#if CV_SSE2
72 Op8 op8;
73#endif
74 Op op;
75
76 for( ; sz.height--; src1 += step1/sizeof(src1[0]),
77 src2 += step2/sizeof(src2[0]),
78 dst += step/sizeof(dst[0]) )
79 {
80 int x = 0;
81
82 #if CV_SSE2
83 if( USE_SSE2 )
84 {
85 for( ; x <= sz.width - 32; x += 32 )
86 {
87 __m128i r0 = _mm_loadu_si128((const __m128i*)(src1 + x));
88 __m128i r1 = _mm_loadu_si128((const __m128i*)(src1 + x + 16));
89 r0 = op8(r0,_mm_loadu_si128((const __m128i*)(src2 + x)));
90 r1 = op8(r1,_mm_loadu_si128((const __m128i*)(src2 + x + 16)));
91 _mm_storeu_si128((__m128i*)(dst + x), r0);
92 _mm_storeu_si128((__m128i*)(dst + x + 16), r1);
93 }
94 for( ; x <= sz.width - 8; x += 8 )
95 {
96 __m128i r0 = _mm_loadl_epi64((const __m128i*)(src1 + x));
97 r0 = op8(r0,_mm_loadl_epi64((const __m128i*)(src2 + x)));
98 _mm_storel_epi64((__m128i*)(dst + x), r0);
99 }
100 }
101 #endif
102#if CV_ENABLE_UNROLLED
103 for( ; x <= sz.width - 4; x += 4 )
104 {
105 T v0 = op(src1[x], src2[x]);
106 T v1 = op(src1[x+1], src2[x+1]);
107 dst[x] = v0; dst[x+1] = v1;
108 v0 = op(src1[x+2], src2[x+2]);
109 v1 = op(src1[x+3], src2[x+3]);
110 dst[x+2] = v0; dst[x+3] = v1;
111 }
112#endif
113 for( ; x < sz.width; x++ )
114 dst[x] = op(src1[x], src2[x]);
115 }
116}

118template<typename T, class Op, class Op16>
119void vBinOp16(const T* src1, size_t step1, const T* src2, size_t step2,
120 T* dst, size_t step, Size sz)
121{
122#if CV_SSE2
123 Op16 op16;
124#endif
125 Op op;
126
127 for( ; sz.height--; src1 += step1/sizeof(src1[0]),
128 src2 += step2/sizeof(src2[0]),
129 dst += step/sizeof(dst[0]) )
130 {
131 int x = 0;
132
133 #if CV_SSE2
134 if( USE_SSE2 )
135 {
136 for( ; x <= sz.width - 16; x += 16 )
137 {
138 __m128i r0 = _mm_loadu_si128((const __m128i*)(src1 + x));
139 __m128i r1 = _mm_loadu_si128((const __m128i*)(src1 + x + 8));
140 r0 = op16(r0,_mm_loadu_si128((const __m128i*)(src2 + x)));
141 r1 = op16(r1,_mm_loadu_si128((const __m128i*)(src2 + x + 8)));
142 _mm_storeu_si128((__m128i*)(dst + x), r0);
143 _mm_storeu_si128((__m128i*)(dst + x + 8), r1);
144 }
145 for( ; x <= sz.width - 4; x += 4 )
146 {
147 __m128i r0 = _mm_loadl_epi64((const __m128i*)(src1 + x));
148 r0 = op16(r0,_mm_loadl_epi64((const __m128i*)(src2 + x)));
149 _mm_storel_epi64((__m128i*)(dst + x), r0);
150 }
151 }
152 else
153 #endif
154
155 for( ; x <= sz.width - 4; x += 4 )
156 {
157 T v0 = op(src1[x], src2[x]);
158 T v1 = op(src1[x+1], src2[x+1]);
159 dst[x] = v0; dst[x+1] = v1;
160 v0 = op(src1[x+2], src2[x+2]);
161 v1 = op(src1[x+3], src2[x+3]);
162 dst[x+2] = v0; dst[x+3] = v1;
163 }
164
165 for( ; x < sz.width; x++ )
166 dst[x] = op(src1[x], src2[x]);
167 }
168}

171template<class Op, class Op32>
172void vBinOp32s(const int* src1, size_t step1, const int* src2, size_t step2,
173 int* dst, size_t step, Size sz)
174{
175#if CV_SSE2
176 Op32 op32;
177#endif
178 Op op;
179
180 for( ; sz.height--; src1 += step1/sizeof(src1[0]),
181 src2 += step2/sizeof(src2[0]),
182 dst += step/sizeof(dst[0]) )
183 {
184 int x = 0;
185
186#if CV_SSE2
187 if( USE_SSE2 )
188 {
189 if( (((size_t)src1|(size_t)src2|(size_t)dst)&15) == 0 )
190 for( ; x <= sz.width - 8; x += 8 )
191 {
192 __m128i r0 = _mm_load_si128((const __m128i*)(src1 + x));
193 __m128i r1 = _mm_load_si128((const __m128i*)(src1 + x + 4));
194 r0 = op32(r0,_mm_load_si128((const __m128i*)(src2 + x)));
195 r1 = op32(r1,_mm_load_si128((const __m128i*)(src2 + x + 4)));
196 _mm_store_si128((__m128i*)(dst + x), r0);
197 _mm_store_si128((__m128i*)(dst + x + 4), r1);
198 }
199 else
200 for( ; x <= sz.width - 8; x += 8 )
201 {
202 __m128i r0 = _mm_loadu_si128((const __m128i*)(src1 + x));
203 __m128i r1 = _mm_loadu_si128((const __m128i*)(src1 + x + 4));
204 r0 = op32(r0,_mm_loadu_si128((const __m128i*)(src2 + x)));
205 r1 = op32(r1,_mm_loadu_si128((const __m128i*)(src2 + x + 4)));
206 _mm_storeu_si128((__m128i*)(dst + x), r0);
207 _mm_storeu_si128((__m128i*)(dst + x + 4), r1);
208 }
209 }
210#endif
211#if CV_ENABLE_UNROLLED
212 for( ; x <= sz.width - 4; x += 4 )
213 {
214 int v0 = op(src1[x], src2[x]);
215 int v1 = op(src1[x+1], src2[x+1]);
216 dst[x] = v0; dst[x+1] = v1;
217 v0 = op(src1[x+2], src2[x+2]);
218 v1 = op(src1[x+3], src2[x+3]);
219 dst[x+2] = v0; dst[x+3] = v1;
220 }
221#endif
222 for( ; x < sz.width; x++ )
223 dst[x] = op(src1[x], src2[x]);
224 }
225}

228template<class Op, class Op32>
229void vBinOp32f(const float* src1, size_t step1, const float* src2, size_t step2,
230 float* dst, size_t step, Size sz)
231{
232#if CV_SSE2
233 Op32 op32;
234#endif
235 Op op;
236
237 for( ; sz.height--; src1 += step1/sizeof(src1[0]),
238 src2 += step2/sizeof(src2[0]),
239 dst += step/sizeof(dst[0]) )
240 {
241 int x = 0;
242
243 #if CV_SSE2
244 if( USE_SSE2 )
245 {
246 if( (((size_t)src1|(size_t)src2|(size_t)dst)&15) == 0 )
247 for( ; x <= sz.width - 8; x += 8 )
248 {
249 __m128 r0 = _mm_load_ps(src1 + x);
250 __m128 r1 = _mm_load_ps(src1 + x + 4);
251 r0 = op32(r0,_mm_load_ps(src2 + x));
252 r1 = op32(r1,_mm_load_ps(src2 + x + 4));
253 _mm_store_ps(dst + x, r0);
254 _mm_store_ps(dst + x + 4, r1);
255 }
256 else
257 for( ; x <= sz.width - 8; x += 8 )
258 {
259 __m128 r0 = _mm_loadu_ps(src1 + x);
260 __m128 r1 = _mm_loadu_ps(src1 + x + 4);
261 r0 = op32(r0,_mm_loadu_ps(src2 + x));
262 r1 = op32(r1,_mm_loadu_ps(src2 + x + 4));
263 _mm_storeu_ps(dst + x, r0);
264 _mm_storeu_ps(dst + x + 4, r1);
265 }
266 }
267 #endif
268#if CV_ENABLE_UNROLLED
269 for( ; x <= sz.width - 4; x += 4 )
270 {
271 float v0 = op(src1[x], src2[x]);
272 float v1 = op(src1[x+1], src2[x+1]);
273 dst[x] = v0; dst[x+1] = v1;
274 v0 = op(src1[x+2], src2[x+2]);
275 v1 = op(src1[x+3], src2[x+3]);
276 dst[x+2] = v0; dst[x+3] = v1;
277 }
278#endif
279 for( ; x < sz.width; x++ )
280 dst[x] = op(src1[x], src2[x]);
281 }
282}

284template<class Op, class Op64>
285void vBinOp64f(const double* src1, size_t step1, const double* src2, size_t step2,
286 double* dst, size_t step, Size sz)
287{
288#if CV_SSE2
289 Op64 op64;
290#endif
291 Op op;
292
293 for( ; sz.height--; src1 += step1/sizeof(src1[0]),
294 src2 += step2/sizeof(src2[0]),
295 dst += step/sizeof(dst[0]) )
296 {
297 int x = 0;
298
299 #if CV_SSE2
300 if( USE_SSE2 && (((size_t)src1|(size_t)src2|(size_t)dst)&15) == 0 )
301 for( ; x <= sz.width - 4; x += 4 )
302 {
303 __m128d r0 = _mm_load_pd(src1 + x);
304 __m128d r1 = _mm_load_pd(src1 + x + 2);
305 r0 = op64(r0,_mm_load_pd(src2 + x));
306 r1 = op64(r1,_mm_load_pd(src2 + x + 2));
307 _mm_store_pd(dst + x, r0);
308 _mm_store_pd(dst + x + 2, r1);
309 }
310 else
311 #endif
312 for( ; x <= sz.width - 4; x += 4 )
313 {
314 double v0 = op(src1[x], src2[x]);
315 double v1 = op(src1[x+1], src2[x+1]);
316 dst[x] = v0; dst[x+1] = v1;
317 v0 = op(src1[x+2], src2[x+2]);
318 v1 = op(src1[x+3], src2[x+3]);
319 dst[x+2] = v0; dst[x+3] = v1;
320 }
321
322 for( ; x < sz.width; x++ )
323 dst[x] = op(src1[x], src2[x]);
324 }
325}

329struct _VAdd8u { __m128i operator()(const __m128i& a, const __m128i& b) const { return _mm_adds_epu8(a,b); }};
330struct _VSub8u { __m128i operator()(const __m128i& a, const __m128i& b) const { return _mm_subs_epu8(a,b); }};
331struct _VMin8u { __m128i operator()(const __m128i& a, const __m128i& b) const { return _mm_min_epu8(a,b); }};
332struct _VMax8u { __m128i operator()(const __m128i& a, const __m128i& b) const { return _mm_max_epu8(a,b); }};
333struct _VAbsDiff8u
334{
335 __m128i operator()(const __m128i& a, const __m128i& b) const
336 { return _mm_add_epi8(_mm_subs_epu8(a,b),_mm_subs_epu8(b,a)); }
337};
338
339struct _VAdd8s { __m128i operator()(const __m128i& a, const __m128i& b) const { return _mm_adds_epi8(a,b); }};
340struct _VSub8s { __m128i operator()(const __m128i& a, const __m128i& b) const { return _mm_subs_epi8(a,b); }};
341struct _VMin8s
342{
343 __m128i operator()(const __m128i& a, const __m128i& b) const
344 {
345 __m128i m = _mm_cmpgt_epi8(a, b);
346 return _mm_xor_si128(a, _mm_and_si128(_mm_xor_si128(a, b), m));
347 }
348};
349struct _VMax8s
350{
351 __m128i operator()(const __m128i& a, const __m128i& b) const
352 {
353 __m128i m = _mm_cmpgt_epi8(b, a);
354 return _mm_xor_si128(a, _mm_and_si128(_mm_xor_si128(a, b), m));
355 }
356};
357struct _VAbsDiff8s
358{
359 __m128i operator()(const __m128i& a, const __m128i& b) const
360 {
361 __m128i d = _mm_subs_epi8(a, b);
362 __m128i m = _mm_cmpgt_epi8(b, a);
363 return _mm_subs_epi8(_mm_xor_si128(d, m), m);
364 }
365};
366
367struct _VAdd16u { __m128i operator()(const __m128i& a, const __m128i& b) const { return _mm_adds_epu16(a,b); }};
368struct _VSub16u { __m128i operator()(const __m128i& a, const __m128i& b) const { return _mm_subs_epu16(a,b); }};
369struct _VMin16u
370{
371 __m128i operator()(const __m128i& a, const __m128i& b) const
372 { return _mm_subs_epu16(a,_mm_subs_epu16(a,b)); }

466template<> inline uchar OpAdd<uchar>::operator ()(uchar a, uchar b) const

469{ return CV_FAST_CAST_8U(a - b); }

530static inline void fixSteps(Size sz, size_t elemSize, size_t& step1, size_t& step2, size_t& step)
531{
532 if( sz.height == 1 )
533 step1 = step2 = step = sz.width*elemSize;
534}
535#if defined(__clang__)
536#pragma clang diagnostic pop
537#endif
538
539static void add8u( const uchar* src1, size_t step1,
540 const uchar* src2, size_t step2,
541 uchar* dst, size_t step, Size sz, void* )
542{
543 IF_IPP(fixSteps(sz, sizeof(dst[0]), step1, step2, step);
544 ippiAdd_8u_C1RSfs(src1, (int)step1, src2, (int)step2, dst, (int)step, ippiSize(sz), 0),
545 (vBinOp8<uchar, OpAdd<uchar>, IF_SIMD(_VAdd8u)>(src1, step1, src2, step2, dst, step, sz)));
546}

964/****************************************************************************************\
965* logical operations *
966\****************************************************************************************/
967
968void convertAndUnrollScalar( const Mat& sc, int buftype, uchar* scbuf, size_t blocksize )
969{
970 int scn = (int)sc.total(), cn = CV_MAT_CN(buftype);
971 size_t esz = CV_ELEM_SIZE(buftype);
972 getConvertFunc(sc.depth(), buftype)(sc.data, 0, 0, 0, scbuf, 0, Size(std::min(cn, scn), 1), 0);
973 // unroll the scalar
974 if( scn < cn )
975 {
976 CV_Assert( scn == 1 );
977 size_t esz1 = CV_ELEM_SIZE1(buftype);
978 for( size_t i = esz1; i < esz; i++ )
979 scbuf[i] = scbuf[i - esz1];
980 }
981 for( size_t i = esz; i < blocksize*esz; i++ )
982 scbuf[i] = scbuf[i - esz];
983}
984
985static void binary_op(InputArray _src1, InputArray _src2, OutputArray _dst,
986 InputArray _mask, const BinaryFunc* tab, bool bitwise)
987{
988 int kind1 = _src1.kind(), kind2 = _src2.kind();
989 Mat src1 = _src1.getMat(), src2 = _src2.getMat();
990 bool haveMask = !_mask.empty(), haveScalar = false;
991 BinaryFunc func;
992 int c;
993
994 if( src1.dims <= 2 && src2.dims <= 2 && kind1 == kind2 &&
995 src1.size() == src2.size() && src1.type() == src2.type() && !haveMask )
996 {
997 _dst.create(src1.size(), src1.type());
998 Mat dst = _dst.getMat();
999 if( bitwise )
1000 {
1001 func = *tab;
1002 c = (int)src1.elemSize();
1003 }
1004 else
1005 {
1006 func = tab[src1.depth()];
1007 c = src1.channels();
1008 }
1009
1010 Size sz = getContinuousSize(src1, src2, dst);
1011 size_t len = sz.width*(size_t)c;
1012 if( len == (size_t)(int)len )
1013 {
1014 sz.width = (int)len;
1015 func(src1.data, src1.step, src2.data, src2.step, dst.data, dst.step, sz, 0);
1016 return;
1017 }
1018 }
1019
1020 if( (kind1 == _InputArray::MATX) + (kind2 == _InputArray::MATX) == 1 ||
1021 src1.size != src2.size || src1.type() != src2.type() )
1022 {
1023 if( checkScalar(src1, src2.type(), kind1, kind2) )
1024 // src1 is a scalar; swap it with src2
1025 swap(src1, src2);
1026 else if( !checkScalar(src2, src1.type(), kind2, kind1) )
1027 CV_Error( CV_StsUnmatchedSizes,
1028 "The operation is neither 'array op array' (where arrays have the same size and type), "
1029 "nor 'array op scalar', nor 'scalar op array'" );
1030 haveScalar = true;
1031 }
1032
1033 size_t esz = src1.elemSize();
1034 size_t blocksize0 = (BLOCK_SIZE + esz-1)/esz;
1035 int cn = src1.channels();
1036 BinaryFunc copymask = 0;
1037 Mat mask;
1038 bool reallocate = false;
1039
1040 if( haveMask )
1041 {
1042 mask = _mask.getMat();
1043 CV_Assert( (mask.type() == CV_8UC1 || mask.type() == CV_8SC1) );
1044 CV_Assert( mask.size == src1.size );
1045 copymask = getCopyMaskFunc(esz);
1046 Mat tdst = _dst.getMat();
1047 reallocate = tdst.size != src1.size || tdst.type() != src1.type();
1048 }
1049
1050 AutoBuffer<uchar> _buf;
1051 uchar *scbuf = 0, *maskbuf = 0;
1052
1053 _dst.create(src1.dims, src1.size, src1.type());
1054 Mat dst = _dst.getMat();
1055
1056 // if this is mask operation and dst has been reallocated,
1057 // we have to
1058 if( haveMask && reallocate )
1059 dst = Scalar::all(0);
1060
1061 if( bitwise )
1062 {
1063 func = *tab;
1064 c = (int)esz;
1065 }
1066 else
1067 {
1068 func = tab[src1.depth()];
1069 c = cn;
1070 }
1071
1072 if( !haveScalar )
1073 {
1074 const Mat* arrays[] = { &src1, &src2, &dst, &mask, 0 };
1075 uchar* ptrs[4];
1076
1077 NAryMatIterator it(arrays, ptrs);
1078 size_t total = it.size, blocksize = total;
1079
1080 if( blocksize*c > INT_MAX )
1081 blocksize = INT_MAX/c;
1082
1083 if( haveMask )
1084 {
1085 blocksize = std::min(blocksize, blocksize0);
1086 _buf.allocate(blocksize*esz);
1087 maskbuf = _buf;
1088 }
1089
1090 for( size_t i = 0; i < it.nplanes; i++, ++it )
1091 {
1092 for( size_t j = 0; j < total; j += blocksize )
1093 {
1094 int bsz = (int)MIN(total - j, blocksize);
1095
1096 func( ptrs[0], 0, ptrs[1], 0, haveMask ? maskbuf : ptrs[2], 0, Size(bsz*c, 1), 0 );
1097 if( haveMask )
1098 {
1099 copymask( maskbuf, 0, ptrs[3], 0, ptrs[2], 0, Size(bsz, 1), &esz );
1100 ptrs[3] += bsz;
1101 }
1102
1103 bsz *= (int)esz;
1104 ptrs[0] += bsz; ptrs[1] += bsz; ptrs[2] += bsz;
1105 }
1106 }
1107 }
1108 else
1109 {
1110 const Mat* arrays[] = { &src1, &dst, &mask, 0 };
1111 uchar* ptrs[3];
1112
1113 NAryMatIterator it(arrays, ptrs);
1114 size_t total = it.size, blocksize = std::min(total, blocksize0);
1115
1116 _buf.allocate(blocksize*(haveMask ? 2 : 1)*esz + 32);
1117 scbuf = _buf;
1118 maskbuf = alignPtr(scbuf + blocksize*esz, 16);
1119
1120 convertAndUnrollScalar( src2, src1.type(), scbuf, blocksize);
1121
1122 for( size_t i = 0; i < it.nplanes; i++, ++it )
1123 {
1124 for( size_t j = 0; j < total; j += blocksize )
1125 {
1126 int bsz = (int)MIN(total - j, blocksize);
1127
1128 func( ptrs[0], 0, scbuf, 0, haveMask ? maskbuf : ptrs[1], 0, Size(bsz*c, 1), 0 );
1129 if( haveMask )
1130 {
1131 copymask( maskbuf, 0, ptrs[2], 0, ptrs[1], 0, Size(bsz, 1), &esz );
1132 ptrs[2] += bsz;
1133 }
1134
1135 bsz *= (int)esz;
1136 ptrs[0] += bsz; ptrs[1] += bsz;
1137 }
1138 }
1139 }
1140}

1237static int actualScalarDepth(const double* data, int len)
1238{
1239 int i = 0, minval = INT_MAX, maxval = INT_MIN;
1240 for(; i < len; ++i)
1241 {
1242 int ival = cvRound(data[i]);
1243 if( ival != data[i] )
1244 break;
1245 minval = MIN(minval, ival);
1246 maxval = MAX(maxval, ival);
1247 }
1248 return i < len ? CV_64F :
1249 minval >= 0 && maxval <= (int)UCHAR_MAX ? CV_8U :
1250 minval >= (int)SCHAR_MIN && maxval <= (int)SCHAR_MAX ? CV_8S :
1251 minval >= 0 && maxval <= (int)USHRT_MAX ? CV_16U :
1252 minval >= (int)SHRT_MIN && maxval <= (int)SHRT_MAX ? CV_16S :
1253 CV_32S;
1254}
1255
1256static void arithm_op(InputArray _src1, InputArray _src2, OutputArray _dst,
1257 InputArray _mask, int dtype, BinaryFunc* tab, bool muldiv=false, void* usrdata=0)
1258{
1259 int kind1 = _src1.kind(), kind2 = _src2.kind();
1260 Mat src1 = _src1.getMat(), src2 = _src2.getMat();
1261 bool haveMask = !_mask.empty();
1262 bool reallocate = false;
1263
1264 bool src1Scalar = checkScalar(src1, src2.type(), kind1, kind2);
1265 bool src2Scalar = checkScalar(src2, src1.type(), kind2, kind1);
1266
1267 if( (kind1 == kind2 || src1.channels() == 1) && src1.dims <= 2 && src2.dims <= 2 &&
1268 src1.size() == src2.size() && src1.type() == src2.type() &&
1269 !haveMask && ((!_dst.fixedType() && (dtype < 0 || CV_MAT_DEPTH(dtype) == src1.depth())) ||
1270 (_dst.fixedType() && _dst.type() == _src1.type())) &&
1271 ((src1Scalar && src2Scalar) || (!src1Scalar && !src2Scalar)) )
1272 {
1273 _dst.create(src1.size(), src1.type());
1274 Mat dst = _dst.getMat();
1275 Size sz = getContinuousSize(src1, src2, dst, src1.channels());
1276 tab[src1.depth()](src1.data, src1.step, src2.data, src2.step, dst.data, dst.step, sz, usrdata);
1277 return;
1278 }
1279
1280 bool haveScalar = false, swapped12 = false;
1281 int depth2 = src2.depth();
1282 if( src1.size != src2.size || src1.channels() != src2.channels() ||
1283 (kind1 == _InputArray::MATX && (src1.size() == Size(1,4) || src1.size() == Size(1,1))) ||
1284 (kind2 == _InputArray::MATX && (src2.size() == Size(1,4) || src2.size() == Size(1,1))) )
1285 {
1286 if( checkScalar(src1, src2.type(), kind1, kind2) )
1287 {
1288 // src1 is a scalar; swap it with src2
1289 swap(src1, src2);
1290 swapped12 = true;
1291 }
1292 else if( !checkScalar(src2, src1.type(), kind2, kind1) )
1293 CV_Error( CV_StsUnmatchedSizes,
1294 "The operation is neither 'array op array' (where arrays have the same size and the same number of channels), "
1295 "nor 'array op scalar', nor 'scalar op array'" );
1296 haveScalar = true;
1297 CV_Assert(src2.type() == CV_64F && (src2.rows == 4 || src2.rows == 1));
1298
1299 if (!muldiv)
1300 {
1301 depth2 = actualScalarDepth(src2.ptr<double>(), src1.channels());
1302 if( depth2 == CV_64F && (src1.depth() < CV_32S || src1.depth() == CV_32F) )
1303 depth2 = CV_32F;
1304 }
1305 else
1306 depth2 = CV_64F;
1307 }
1308
1309 int cn = src1.channels(), depth1 = src1.depth(), wtype;
1310 BinaryFunc cvtsrc1 = 0, cvtsrc2 = 0, cvtdst = 0;
1311
1312 if( dtype < 0 )
1313 {
1314 if( _dst.fixedType() )
1315 dtype = _dst.type();
1316 else
1317 {
1318 if( !haveScalar && src1.type() != src2.type() )
1319 CV_Error(CV_StsBadArg,
1320 "When the input arrays in add/subtract/multiply/divide functions have different types, "
1321 "the output array type must be explicitly specified");
1322 dtype = src1.type();
1323 }
1324 }
1325 dtype = CV_MAT_DEPTH(dtype);
1326
1327 if( depth1 == depth2 && dtype == depth1 )
1328 wtype = dtype;
1329 else if( !muldiv )
1330 {
1331 wtype = depth1 <= CV_8S && depth2 <= CV_8S ? CV_16S :
1332 depth1 <= CV_32S && depth2 <= CV_32S ? CV_32S : std::max(depth1, depth2);
1333 wtype = std::max(wtype, dtype);
1334
1335 // when the result of addition should be converted to an integer type,
1336 // and just one of the input arrays is floating-point, it makes sense to convert that input to integer type before the operation,
1337 // instead of converting the other input to floating-point and then converting the operation result back to integers.
1338 if( dtype < CV_32F && (depth1 < CV_32F || depth2 < CV_32F) )
1339 wtype = CV_32S;
1340 }
1341 else
1342 {
1343 wtype = std::max(depth1, std::max(depth2, CV_32F));
1344 wtype = std::max(wtype, dtype);
1345 }
1346
1347 cvtsrc1 = depth1 == wtype ? 0 : getConvertFunc(depth1, wtype);
1348 cvtsrc2 = depth2 == depth1 ? cvtsrc1 : depth2 == wtype ? 0 : getConvertFunc(depth2, wtype);
1349 cvtdst = dtype == wtype ? 0 : getConvertFunc(wtype, dtype);
1350
1351 dtype = CV_MAKETYPE(dtype, cn);
1352 wtype = CV_MAKETYPE(wtype, cn);
1353
1354 size_t esz1 = src1.elemSize(), esz2 = src2.elemSize();
1355 size_t dsz = CV_ELEM_SIZE(dtype), wsz = CV_ELEM_SIZE(wtype);
1356 size_t blocksize0 = (size_t)(BLOCK_SIZE + wsz-1)/wsz;
1357 BinaryFunc copymask = 0;
1358 Mat mask;
1359
1360 if( haveMask )
1361 {
1362 mask = _mask.getMat();
1363 CV_Assert( (mask.type() == CV_8UC1 || mask.type() == CV_8SC1) );
1364 CV_Assert( mask.size == src1.size );
1365 copymask = getCopyMaskFunc(dsz);
1366 Mat tdst = _dst.getMat();
1367 reallocate = tdst.size != src1.size || tdst.type() != dtype;
1368 }
1369
1370 AutoBuffer<uchar> _buf;
1371 uchar *buf, *maskbuf = 0, *buf1 = 0, *buf2 = 0, *wbuf = 0;
1372 size_t bufesz = (cvtsrc1 ? wsz : 0) + (cvtsrc2 || haveScalar ? wsz : 0) + (cvtdst ? wsz : 0) + (haveMask ? dsz : 0);
1373
1374 _dst.create(src1.dims, src1.size, dtype);
1375 Mat dst = _dst.getMat();
1376
1377 if( haveMask && reallocate )
1378 dst = Scalar::all(0);
1379
1380 BinaryFunc func = tab[CV_MAT_DEPTH(wtype)];
1381
1382 if( !haveScalar )
1383 {
1384 const Mat* arrays[] = { &src1, &src2, &dst, &mask, 0 };
1385 uchar* ptrs[4];
1386
1387 NAryMatIterator it(arrays, ptrs);
1388 size_t total = it.size, blocksize = total;
1389
1390 if( haveMask || cvtsrc1 || cvtsrc2 || cvtdst )
1391 blocksize = std::min(blocksize, blocksize0);
1392
1393 _buf.allocate(bufesz*blocksize + 64);
1394 buf = _buf;
1395 if( cvtsrc1 )
1396 buf1 = buf, buf = alignPtr(buf + blocksize*wsz, 16);
1397 if( cvtsrc2 )
1398 buf2 = buf, buf = alignPtr(buf + blocksize*wsz, 16);
1399 wbuf = maskbuf = buf;
1400 if( cvtdst )
1401 buf = alignPtr(buf + blocksize*wsz, 16);
1402 if( haveMask )
1403 maskbuf = buf;
1404
1405 for( size_t i = 0; i < it.nplanes; i++, ++it )
1406 {
1407 for( size_t j = 0; j < total; j += blocksize )
1408 {
1409 int bsz = (int)MIN(total - j, blocksize);
1410 Size bszn(bsz*cn, 1);
1411 const uchar *sptr1 = ptrs[0], *sptr2 = ptrs[1];
1412 uchar* dptr = ptrs[2];
1413 if( cvtsrc1 )
1414 {
1415 cvtsrc1( sptr1, 0, 0, 0, buf1, 0, bszn, 0 );
1416 sptr1 = buf1;
1417 }
1418 if( ptrs[0] == ptrs[1] )
1419 sptr2 = sptr1;
1420 else if( cvtsrc2 )
1421 {
1422 cvtsrc2( sptr2, 0, 0, 0, buf2, 0, bszn, 0 );
1423 sptr2 = buf2;
1424 }
1425
1426 if( !haveMask && !cvtdst )
1427 func( sptr1, 0, sptr2, 0, dptr, 0, bszn, usrdata );
1428 else
1429 {
1430 func( sptr1, 0, sptr2, 0, wbuf, 0, bszn, usrdata );
1431 if( !haveMask )
1432 cvtdst( wbuf, 0, 0, 0, dptr, 0, bszn, 0 );
1433 else if( !cvtdst )
1434 {
1435 copymask( wbuf, 0, ptrs[3], 0, dptr, 0, Size(bsz, 1), &dsz );
1436 ptrs[3] += bsz;
1437 }
1438 else
1439 {
1440 cvtdst( wbuf, 0, 0, 0, maskbuf, 0, bszn, 0 );
1441 copymask( maskbuf, 0, ptrs[3], 0, dptr, 0, Size(bsz, 1), &dsz );
1442 ptrs[3] += bsz;
1443 }
1444 }
1445 ptrs[0] += bsz*esz1; ptrs[1] += bsz*esz2; ptrs[2] += bsz*dsz;
1446 }
1447 }
1448 }
1449 else
1450 {
1451 const Mat* arrays[] = { &src1, &dst, &mask, 0 };
1452 uchar* ptrs[3];
1453
1454 NAryMatIterator it(arrays, ptrs);
1455 size_t total = it.size, blocksize = std::min(total, blocksize0);
1456
1457 _buf.allocate(bufesz*blocksize + 64);
1458 buf = _buf;
1459 if( cvtsrc1 )
1460 buf1 = buf, buf = alignPtr(buf + blocksize*wsz, 16);
1461 buf2 = buf; buf = alignPtr(buf + blocksize*wsz, 16);
1462 wbuf = maskbuf = buf;
1463 if( cvtdst )
1464 buf = alignPtr(buf + blocksize*wsz, 16);
1465 if( haveMask )
1466 maskbuf = buf;
1467
1468 convertAndUnrollScalar( src2, wtype, buf2, blocksize);
1469
1470 for( size_t i = 0; i < it.nplanes; i++, ++it )
1471 {
1472 for( size_t j = 0; j < total; j += blocksize )
1473 {
1474 int bsz = (int)MIN(total - j, blocksize);
1475 Size bszn(bsz*cn, 1);
1476 const uchar *sptr1 = ptrs[0];
1477 const uchar* sptr2 = buf2;
1478 uchar* dptr = ptrs[1];
1479
1480 if( cvtsrc1 )
1481 {
1482 cvtsrc1( sptr1, 0, 0, 0, buf1, 0, bszn, 0 );
1483 sptr1 = buf1;
1484 }
1485
1486 if( swapped12 )
1487 std::swap(sptr1, sptr2);
1488
1489 if( !haveMask && !cvtdst )
1490 func( sptr1, 0, sptr2, 0, dptr, 0, bszn, usrdata );
1491 else
1492 {
1493 func( sptr1, 0, sptr2, 0, wbuf, 0, bszn, usrdata );
1494 if( !haveMask )
1495 cvtdst( wbuf, 0, 0, 0, dptr, 0, bszn, 0 );
1496 else if( !cvtdst )
1497 {
1498 copymask( wbuf, 0, ptrs[2], 0, dptr, 0, Size(bsz, 1), &dsz );
1499 ptrs[2] += bsz;
1500 }
1501 else
1502 {
1503 cvtdst( wbuf, 0, 0, 0, maskbuf, 0, bszn, 0 );
1504 copymask( maskbuf, 0, ptrs[2], 0, dptr, 0, Size(bsz, 1), &dsz );
1505 ptrs[2] += bsz;
1506 }
1507 }
1508 ptrs[0] += bsz*esz1; ptrs[1] += bsz*dsz;
1509 }
1510 }
1511 }
1512}

1563
1564void cv::subtract( InputArray _src1, InputArray _src2, OutputArray _dst,
1565 InputArray mask, int dtype )
1566{
1567#ifdef HAVE_TEGRA_OPTIMIZATION
1568 int kind1 = _src1.kind(), kind2 = _src2.kind();
1569 Mat src1 = _src1.getMat(), src2 = _src2.getMat();
1570 bool src1Scalar = checkScalar(src1, _src2.type(), kind1, kind2);
1571 bool src2Scalar = checkScalar(src2, _src1.type(), kind2, kind1);
1572
1573 if (!src1Scalar && !src2Scalar &&
1574 src1.depth() == CV_8U && src2.type() == src1.type() &&
1575 src1.dims == 2 && src2.size() == src1.size() &&
1576 mask.empty())
1577 {
1578 if (dtype < 0)
1579 {
1580 if (_dst.fixedType())
1581 {
1582 dtype = _dst.depth();
1583 }
1584 else
1585 {
1586 dtype = src1.depth();
1587 }
1588 }
1589
1590 dtype = CV_MAT_DEPTH(dtype);
1591
1592 if (!_dst.fixedType() || dtype == _dst.depth())
1593 {
1594 _dst.create(src1.size(), CV_MAKE_TYPE(dtype, src1.channels()));
1595
1596 if (dtype == CV_16S)
1597 {
1598 Mat dst = _dst.getMat();
1599 if(tegra::subtract_8u8u16s(src1, src2, dst))
1600 return;
1601 }
1602 else if (dtype == CV_32F)
1603 {
1604 Mat dst = _dst.getMat();
1605 if(tegra::subtract_8u8u32f(src1, src2, dst))
1606 return;
1607 }
1608 else if (dtype == CV_8S)
1609 {
1610 Mat dst = _dst.getMat();
1611 if(tegra::subtract_8u8u8s(src1, src2, dst))
1612 return;
1613 }
1614 }
1615 }
1616#endif
1617 arithm_op(_src1, _src2, _dst, mask, dtype, getSubTab() );
1618}
1619
1620void cv::absdiff( InputArray src1, InputArray src2, OutputArray dst )
1621{
1622 arithm_op(src1, src2, dst, noArray(), -1, getAbsDiffTab());
1623}

1632template<typename T, typename WT> static void
1633mul_( const T* src1, size_t step1, const T* src2, size_t step2,
1634 T* dst, size_t step, Size size, WT scale )
1635{
1636 step1 /= sizeof(src1[0]);
1637 step2 /= sizeof(src2[0]);
1638 step /= sizeof(dst[0]);
1639
1640 if( scale == (WT)1. )
1641 {
1642 for( ; size.height--; src1 += step1, src2 += step2, dst += step )
1643 {
1644 int i=0;
1645 #if CV_ENABLE_UNROLLED
1646 for(; i <= size.width - 4; i += 4 )
1647 {
1648 T t0;
1649 T t1;
1650 t0 = saturate_cast<T>(src1[i ] * src2[i ]);
1651 t1 = saturate_cast<T>(src1[i+1] * src2[i+1]);
1652 dst[i ] = t0;
1653 dst[i+1] = t1;
1654
1655 t0 = saturate_cast<T>(src1[i+2] * src2[i+2]);
1656 t1 = saturate_cast<T>(src1[i+3] * src2[i+3]);
1657 dst[i+2] = t0;
1658 dst[i+3] = t1;
1659 }
1660 #endif
1661 for( ; i < size.width; i++ )
1662 dst[i] = saturate_cast<T>(src1[i] * src2[i]);
1663 }
1664 }
1665 else
1666 {
1667 for( ; size.height--; src1 += step1, src2 += step2, dst += step )
1668 {
1669 int i = 0;
1670 #if CV_ENABLE_UNROLLED
1671 for(; i <= size.width - 4; i += 4 )
1672 {
1673 T t0 = saturate_cast<T>(scale*(WT)src1[i]*src2[i]);
1674 T t1 = saturate_cast<T>(scale*(WT)src1[i+1]*src2[i+1]);
1675 dst[i] = t0; dst[i+1] = t1;
1676
1677 t0 = saturate_cast<T>(scale*(WT)src1[i+2]*src2[i+2]);
1678 t1 = saturate_cast<T>(scale*(WT)src1[i+3]*src2[i+3]);
1679 dst[i+2] = t0; dst[i+3] = t1;
1680 }
1681 #endif
1682 for( ; i < size.width; i++ )
1683 dst[i] = saturate_cast<T>(scale*(WT)src1[i]*src2[i]);
1684 }
1685 }
1686}
1687
1688template<typename T> static void
1689div_( const T* src1, size_t step1, const T* src2, size_t step2,
1690 T* dst, size_t step, Size size, double scale )
1691{
1692 step1 /= sizeof(src1[0]);
1693 step2 /= sizeof(src2[0]);
1694 step /= sizeof(dst[0]);
1695
1696 for( ; size.height--; src1 += step1, src2 += step2, dst += step )
1697 {
1698 int i = 0;
1699 #if CV_ENABLE_UNROLLED
1700 for( ; i <= size.width - 4; i += 4 )
1701 {
1702 if( src2[i] != 0 && src2[i+1] != 0 && src2[i+2] != 0 && src2[i+3] != 0 )
1703 {
1704 double a = (double)src2[i] * src2[i+1];
1705 double b = (double)src2[i+2] * src2[i+3];
1706 double d = scale/(a * b);
1707 b *= d;
1708 a *= d;
1709
1710 T z0 = saturate_cast<T>(src2[i+1] * ((double)src1[i] * b));
1711 T z1 = saturate_cast<T>(src2[i] * ((double)src1[i+1] * b));
1712 T z2 = saturate_cast<T>(src2[i+3] * ((double)src1[i+2] * a));
1713 T z3 = saturate_cast<T>(src2[i+2] * ((double)src1[i+3] * a));
1714
1715 dst[i] = z0; dst[i+1] = z1;
1716 dst[i+2] = z2; dst[i+3] = z3;
1717 }
1718 else
1719 {
1720 T z0 = src2[i] != 0 ? saturate_cast<T>(src1[i]*scale/src2[i]) : 0;
1721 T z1 = src2[i+1] != 0 ? saturate_cast<T>(src1[i+1]*scale/src2[i+1]) : 0;
1722 T z2 = src2[i+2] != 0 ? saturate_cast<T>(src1[i+2]*scale/src2[i+2]) : 0;
1723 T z3 = src2[i+3] != 0 ? saturate_cast<T>(src1[i+3]*scale/src2[i+3]) : 0;
1724
1725 dst[i] = z0; dst[i+1] = z1;
1726 dst[i+2] = z2; dst[i+3] = z3;
1727 }
1728 }
1729 #endif
1730 for( ; i < size.width; i++ )
1731 dst[i] = src2[i] != 0 ? saturate_cast<T>(src1[i]*scale/src2[i]) : 0;
1732 }
1733}
1734
1735template<typename T> static void
1736recip_( const T*, size_t, const T* src2, size_t step2,
1737 T* dst, size_t step, Size size, double scale )
1738{
1739 step2 /= sizeof(src2[0]);
1740 step /= sizeof(dst[0]);
1741
1742 for( ; size.height--; src2 += step2, dst += step )
1743 {
1744 int i = 0;
1745 #if CV_ENABLE_UNROLLED
1746 for( ; i <= size.width - 4; i += 4 )
1747 {
1748 if( src2[i] != 0 && src2[i+1] != 0 && src2[i+2] != 0 && src2[i+3] != 0 )
1749 {
1750 double a = (double)src2[i] * src2[i+1];
1751 double b = (double)src2[i+2] * src2[i+3];
1752 double d = scale/(a * b);
1753 b *= d;
1754 a *= d;
1755
1756 T z0 = saturate_cast<T>(src2[i+1] * b);
1757 T z1 = saturate_cast<T>(src2[i] * b);
1758 T z2 = saturate_cast<T>(src2[i+3] * a);
1759 T z3 = saturate_cast<T>(src2[i+2] * a);
1760
1761 dst[i] = z0; dst[i+1] = z1;
1762 dst[i+2] = z2; dst[i+3] = z3;
1763 }
1764 else
1765 {
1766 T z0 = src2[i] != 0 ? saturate_cast<T>(scale/src2[i]) : 0;
1767 T z1 = src2[i+1] != 0 ? saturate_cast<T>(scale/src2[i+1]) : 0;
1768 T z2 = src2[i+2] != 0 ? saturate_cast<T>(scale/src2[i+2]) : 0;
1769 T z3 = src2[i+3] != 0 ? saturate_cast<T>(scale/src2[i+3]) : 0;
1770
1771 dst[i] = z0; dst[i+1] = z1;
1772 dst[i+2] = z2; dst[i+3] = z3;
1773 }
1774 }
1775 #endif
1776 for( ; i < size.width; i++ )
1777 dst[i] = src2[i] != 0 ? saturate_cast<T>(scale/src2[i]) : 0;
1778 }
1779}

1969* addWeighted *
1970\****************************************************************************************/

1974
1975template<typename T, typename WT> static void
1976addWeighted_( const T* src1, size_t step1, const T* src2, size_t step2,
1977 T* dst, size_t step, Size size, void* _scalars )
1978{
1979 const double* scalars = (const double*)_scalars;
1980 WT alpha = (WT)scalars[0], beta = (WT)scalars[1], gamma = (WT)scalars[2];
1981 step1 /= sizeof(src1[0]);
1982 step2 /= sizeof(src2[0]);
1983 step /= sizeof(dst[0]);
1984
1985 for( ; size.height--; src1 += step1, src2 += step2, dst += step )
1986 {
1987 int x = 0;
1988 #if CV_ENABLE_UNROLLED
1989 for( ; x <= size.width - 4; x += 4 )
1990 {
1991 T t0 = saturate_cast<T>(src1[x]*alpha + src2[x]*beta + gamma);
1992 T t1 = saturate_cast<T>(src1[x+1]*alpha + src2[x+1]*beta + gamma);
1993 dst[x] = t0; dst[x+1] = t1;
1994
1995 t0 = saturate_cast<T>(src1[x+2]*alpha + src2[x+2]*beta + gamma);
1996 t1 = saturate_cast<T>(src1[x+3]*alpha + src2[x+3]*beta + gamma);
1997 dst[x+2] = t0; dst[x+3] = t1;
1998 }
1999 #endif
2000 for( ; x < size.width; x++ )
2001 dst[x] = saturate_cast<T>(src1[x]*alpha + src2[x]*beta + gamma);
2002 }
2003}
2004
2005
2006static void
2007addWeighted8u( const uchar* src1, size_t step1,
2008 const uchar* src2, size_t step2,
2009 uchar* dst, size_t step, Size size,
2010 void* _scalars )
2011{
2012 const double* scalars = (const double*)_scalars;
2013 float alpha = (float)scalars[0], beta = (float)scalars[1], gamma = (float)scalars[2];
2014
2015 for( ; size.height--; src1 += step1, src2 += step2, dst += step )
2016 {
2017 int x = 0;
2018
2019#if CV_SSE2
2020 if( USE_SSE2 )
2021 {
2022 __m128 a4 = _mm_set1_ps(alpha), b4 = _mm_set1_ps(beta), g4 = _mm_set1_ps(gamma);
2023 __m128i z = _mm_setzero_si128();
2024
2025 for( ; x <= size.width - 8; x += 8 )
2026 {
2027 __m128i u = _mm_unpacklo_epi8(_mm_loadl_epi64((const __m128i*)(src1 + x)), z);
2028 __m128i v = _mm_unpacklo_epi8(_mm_loadl_epi64((const __m128i*)(src2 + x)), z);
2029
2030 __m128 u0 = _mm_cvtepi32_ps(_mm_unpacklo_epi16(u, z));
2031 __m128 u1 = _mm_cvtepi32_ps(_mm_unpackhi_epi16(u, z));
2032 __m128 v0 = _mm_cvtepi32_ps(_mm_unpacklo_epi16(v, z));
2033 __m128 v1 = _mm_cvtepi32_ps(_mm_unpackhi_epi16(v, z));
2034
2035 u0 = _mm_add_ps(_mm_mul_ps(u0, a4), _mm_mul_ps(v0, b4));
2036 u1 = _mm_add_ps(_mm_mul_ps(u1, a4), _mm_mul_ps(v1, b4));
2037 u0 = _mm_add_ps(u0, g4); u1 = _mm_add_ps(u1, g4);
2038
2039 u = _mm_packs_epi32(_mm_cvtps_epi32(u0), _mm_cvtps_epi32(u1));
2040 u = _mm_packus_epi16(u, u);
2041
2042 _mm_storel_epi64((__m128i*)(dst + x), u);
2043 }
2044 }
2045#endif
2046 #if CV_ENABLE_UNROLLED
2047 for( ; x <= size.width - 4; x += 4 )
2048 {
2049 float t0, t1;
2050 t0 = CV_8TO32F(src1[x])*alpha + CV_8TO32F(src2[x])*beta + gamma;
2051 t1 = CV_8TO32F(src1[x+1])*alpha + CV_8TO32F(src2[x+1])*beta + gamma;
2052
2053 dst[x] = saturate_cast<uchar>(t0);
2054 dst[x+1] = saturate_cast<uchar>(t1);
2055
2056 t0 = CV_8TO32F(src1[x+2])*alpha + CV_8TO32F(src2[x+2])*beta + gamma;
2057 t1 = CV_8TO32F(src1[x+3])*alpha + CV_8TO32F(src2[x+3])*beta + gamma;
2058
2059 dst[x+2] = saturate_cast<uchar>(t0);
2060 dst[x+3] = saturate_cast<uchar>(t1);
2061 }
2062 #endif
2063
2064 for( ; x < size.width; x++ )
2065 {
2066 float t0 = CV_8TO32F(src1[x])*alpha + CV_8TO32F(src2[x])*beta + gamma;
2067 dst[x] = saturate_cast<uchar>(t0);
2068 }
2069 }
2070}

2131* compare *
2132\****************************************************************************************/

2136
2137template<typename T> static void
2138cmp_(const T* src1, size_t step1, const T* src2, size_t step2,
2139 uchar* dst, size_t step, Size size, int code)
2140{
2141 step1 /= sizeof(src1[0]);
2142 step2 /= sizeof(src2[0]);
2143 if( code == CMP_GE || code == CMP_LT )
2144 {
2145 std::swap(src1, src2);
2146 std::swap(step1, step2);
2147 code = code == CMP_GE ? CMP_LE : CMP_GT;
2148 }
2149
2150 if( code == CMP_GT || code == CMP_LE )
2151 {
2152 int m = code == CMP_GT ? 0 : 255;
2153 for( ; size.height--; src1 += step1, src2 += step2, dst += step )
2154 {
2155 int x = 0;
2156 #if CV_ENABLE_UNROLLED
2157 for( ; x <= size.width - 4; x += 4 )
2158 {
2159 int t0, t1;
2160 t0 = -(src1[x] > src2[x]) ^ m;
2161 t1 = -(src1[x+1] > src2[x+1]) ^ m;
2162 dst[x] = (uchar)t0; dst[x+1] = (uchar)t1;
2163 t0 = -(src1[x+2] > src2[x+2]) ^ m;
2164 t1 = -(src1[x+3] > src2[x+3]) ^ m;
2165 dst[x+2] = (uchar)t0; dst[x+3] = (uchar)t1;
2166 }
2167 #endif
2168 for( ; x < size.width; x++ )
2169 dst[x] = (uchar)(-(src1[x] > src2[x]) ^ m);
2170 }
2171 }
2172 else if( code == CMP_EQ || code == CMP_NE )
2173 {
2174 int m = code == CMP_EQ ? 0 : 255;
2175 for( ; size.height--; src1 += step1, src2 += step2, dst += step )
2176 {
2177 int x = 0;
2178 #if CV_ENABLE_UNROLLED
2179 for( ; x <= size.width - 4; x += 4 )
2180 {
2181 int t0, t1;
2182 t0 = -(src1[x] == src2[x]) ^ m;
2183 t1 = -(src1[x+1] == src2[x+1]) ^ m;
2184 dst[x] = (uchar)t0; dst[x+1] = (uchar)t1;
2185 t0 = -(src1[x+2] == src2[x+2]) ^ m;
2186 t1 = -(src1[x+3] == src2[x+3]) ^ m;
2187 dst[x+2] = (uchar)t0; dst[x+3] = (uchar)t1;
2188 }
2189 #endif
2190 for( ; x < size.width; x++ )
2191 dst[x] = (uchar)(-(src1[x] == src2[x]) ^ m);
2192 }
2193 }
2194}

2196#if ARITHM_USE_IPP
2197inline static IppCmpOp convert_cmp(int _cmpop)
2198{
2199 return _cmpop == CMP_EQ ? ippCmpEq :
2200 _cmpop == CMP_GT ? ippCmpGreater :
2201 _cmpop == CMP_GE ? ippCmpGreaterEq :
2202 _cmpop == CMP_LT ? ippCmpLess :
2203 _cmpop == CMP_LE ? ippCmpLessEq :
2204 (IppCmpOp)-1;
2205}
2206#endif

2208static void cmp8u(const uchar* src1, size_t step1, const uchar* src2, size_t step2,
2209 uchar* dst, size_t step, Size size, void* _cmpop)
2210{
2211#if ARITHM_USE_IPP
2212 IppCmpOp op = convert_cmp(*(int *)_cmpop);
2213 if( op >= 0 )
2214 {
2215 fixSteps(size, sizeof(dst[0]), step1, step2, step);
2216 if( ippiCompare_8u_C1R(src1, (int)step1, src2, (int)step2, dst, (int)step, ippiSize(size), op) >= 0 )
2217 return;
2218 }
2219#endif
2220 //vz optimized cmp_(src1, step1, src2, step2, dst, step, size, *(int*)_cmpop);
2221 int code = *(int*)_cmpop;
2222 step1 /= sizeof(src1[0]);
2223 step2 /= sizeof(src2[0]);
2224 if( code == CMP_GE || code == CMP_LT )
2225 {
2226 std::swap(src1, src2);
2227 std::swap(step1, step2);
2228 code = code == CMP_GE ? CMP_LE : CMP_GT;
2229 }
2230
2231 if( code == CMP_GT || code == CMP_LE )
2232 {
2233 int m = code == CMP_GT ? 0 : 255;
2234 for( ; size.height--; src1 += step1, src2 += step2, dst += step )
2235 {
2236 int x =0;
2237 #if CV_SSE2
2238 if( USE_SSE2 ){
2239 __m128i m128 = code == CMP_GT ? _mm_setzero_si128() : _mm_set1_epi8 (-1);
2240 __m128i c128 = _mm_set1_epi8 (-128);
2241 for( ; x <= size.width - 16; x += 16 )
2242 {
2243 __m128i r00 = _mm_loadu_si128((const __m128i*)(src1 + x));
2244 __m128i r10 = _mm_loadu_si128((const __m128i*)(src2 + x));
2245 // no simd for 8u comparison, that's why we need the trick
2246 r00 = _mm_sub_epi8(r00,c128);
2247 r10 = _mm_sub_epi8(r10,c128);
2248
2249 r00 =_mm_xor_si128(_mm_cmpgt_epi8(r00, r10), m128);
2250 _mm_storeu_si128((__m128i*)(dst + x),r00);
2251
2252 }
2253 }
2254 #endif
2255
2256 for( ; x < size.width; x++ ){
2257 dst[x] = (uchar)(-(src1[x] > src2[x]) ^ m);
2258 }
2259 }
2260 }
2261 else if( code == CMP_EQ || code == CMP_NE )
2262 {
2263 int m = code == CMP_EQ ? 0 : 255;
2264 for( ; size.height--; src1 += step1, src2 += step2, dst += step )
2265 {
2266 int x = 0;
2267 #if CV_SSE2
2268 if( USE_SSE2 ){
2269 __m128i m128 = code == CMP_EQ ? _mm_setzero_si128() : _mm_set1_epi8 (-1);
2270 for( ; x <= size.width - 16; x += 16 )
2271 {
2272 __m128i r00 = _mm_loadu_si128((const __m128i*)(src1 + x));
2273 __m128i r10 = _mm_loadu_si128((const __m128i*)(src2 + x));
2274 r00 = _mm_xor_si128 ( _mm_cmpeq_epi8 (r00, r10), m128);
2275 _mm_storeu_si128((__m128i*)(dst + x), r00);
2276 }
2277 }
2278 #endif
2279 for( ; x < size.width; x++ )
2280 dst[x] = (uchar)(-(src1[x] == src2[x]) ^ m);
2281 }
2282 }

2321 step1 /= sizeof(src1[0]);
2322 step2 /= sizeof(src2[0]);
2323 if( code == CMP_GE || code == CMP_LT )
2324 {
2325 std::swap(src1, src2);
2326 std::swap(step1, step2);

2330 if( code == CMP_GT || code == CMP_LE )

2433static BinaryFunc getCmpFunc(int depth)
2434{
2435 static BinaryFunc cmpTab[] =
2436 {
2437 (BinaryFunc)GET_OPTIMIZED(cmp8u), (BinaryFunc)GET_OPTIMIZED(cmp8s),
2438 (BinaryFunc)GET_OPTIMIZED(cmp16u), (BinaryFunc)GET_OPTIMIZED(cmp16s),
2439 (BinaryFunc)GET_OPTIMIZED(cmp32s),
2440 (BinaryFunc)GET_OPTIMIZED(cmp32f), (BinaryFunc)cmp64f,
2441 0
2442 };
2443
2444 return cmpTab[depth];
2445}

2461void cv::compare(InputArray _src1, InputArray _src2, OutputArray _dst, int op)
2462{
2463 CV_Assert( op == CMP_LT || op == CMP_LE || op == CMP_EQ ||
2464 op == CMP_NE || op == CMP_GE || op == CMP_GT );
2465
2466 int kind1 = _src1.kind(), kind2 = _src2.kind();
2467 Mat src1 = _src1.getMat(), src2 = _src2.getMat();
2468
2469 if( kind1 == kind2 && src1.dims <= 2 && src2.dims <= 2 && src1.size() == src2.size() && src1.type() == src2.type() )
2470 {
2471 int cn = src1.channels();
2472 _dst.create(src1.size(), CV_8UC(cn));
2473 Mat dst = _dst.getMat();
2474 Size sz = getContinuousSize(src1, src2, dst, src1.channels());
2475 getCmpFunc(src1.depth())(src1.data, src1.step, src2.data, src2.step, dst.data, dst.step, sz, &op);
2476 return;
2477 }
2478
2479 bool haveScalar = false;
2480
2481 if( (kind1 == _InputArray::MATX) + (kind2 == _InputArray::MATX) == 1 ||
2482 src1.size != src2.size || src1.type() != src2.type() )
2483 {
2484 if( checkScalar(src1, src2.type(), kind1, kind2) )
2485 {
2486 // src1 is a scalar; swap it with src2
2487 swap(src1, src2);
2488 op = op == CMP_LT ? CMP_GT : op == CMP_LE ? CMP_GE :
2489 op == CMP_GE ? CMP_LE : op == CMP_GT ? CMP_LT : op;
2490 }
2491 else if( !checkScalar(src2, src1.type(), kind2, kind1) )
2492 CV_Error( CV_StsUnmatchedSizes,
2493 "The operation is neither 'array op array' (where arrays have the same size and the same type), "
2494 "nor 'array op scalar', nor 'scalar op array'" );
2495 haveScalar = true;
2496 }
2497
2498
2499 int cn = src1.channels(), depth1 = src1.depth(), depth2 = src2.depth();
2500
2501 _dst.create(src1.dims, src1.size, CV_8UC(cn));
2502 src1 = src1.reshape(1); src2 = src2.reshape(1);
2503 Mat dst = _dst.getMat().reshape(1);
2504
2505 size_t esz = src1.elemSize();
2506 size_t blocksize0 = (size_t)(BLOCK_SIZE + esz-1)/esz;
2507 BinaryFunc func = getCmpFunc(depth1);
2508
2509 if( !haveScalar )
2510 {
2511 const Mat* arrays[] = { &src1, &src2, &dst, 0 };
2512 uchar* ptrs[3];
2513
2514 NAryMatIterator it(arrays, ptrs);
2515 size_t total = it.size;
2516
2517 for( size_t i = 0; i < it.nplanes; i++, ++it )
2518 func( ptrs[0], 0, ptrs[1], 0, ptrs[2], 0, Size((int)total, 1), &op );
2519 }
2520 else
2521 {
2522 const Mat* arrays[] = { &src1, &dst, 0 };
2523 uchar* ptrs[2];
2524
2525 NAryMatIterator it(arrays, ptrs);
2526 size_t total = it.size, blocksize = std::min(total, blocksize0);
2527
2528 AutoBuffer<uchar> _buf(blocksize*esz);
2529 uchar *buf = _buf;
2530
2531 if( depth1 > CV_32S )
2532 convertAndUnrollScalar( src2, depth1, buf, blocksize );
2533 else
2534 {
2535 double fval=0;
2536 getConvertFunc(depth2, CV_64F)(src2.data, 0, 0, 0, (uchar*)&fval, 0, Size(1,1), 0);
2537 if( fval < getMinVal(depth1) )
2538 {
2539 dst = Scalar::all(op == CMP_GT || op == CMP_GE || op == CMP_NE ? 255 : 0);
2540 return;
2541 }
2542
2543 if( fval > getMaxVal(depth1) )
2544 {
2545 dst = Scalar::all(op == CMP_LT || op == CMP_LE || op == CMP_NE ? 255 : 0);
2546 return;
2547 }
2548
2549 int ival = cvRound(fval);
2550 if( fval != ival )
2551 {
2552 if( op == CMP_LT || op == CMP_GE )
2553 ival = cvCeil(fval);
2554 else if( op == CMP_LE || op == CMP_GT )
2555 ival = cvFloor(fval);
2556 else
2557 {
2558 dst = Scalar::all(op == CMP_NE ? 255 : 0);
2559 return;
2560 }
2561 }
2562 convertAndUnrollScalar(Mat(1, 1, CV_32S, &ival), depth1, buf, blocksize);
2563 }
2564
2565 for( size_t i = 0; i < it.nplanes; i++, ++it )
2566 {
2567 for( size_t j = 0; j < total; j += blocksize )
2568 {
2569 int bsz = (int)MIN(total - j, blocksize);
2570 func( ptrs[0], 0, buf, 0, ptrs[1], 0, Size(bsz, 1), &op);
2571 ptrs[0] += bsz*esz;
2572 ptrs[1] += bsz;
2573 }
2574 }
2575 }
2576}

2585template<typename T> static void
2586inRange_(const T* src1, size_t step1, const T* src2, size_t step2,
2587 const T* src3, size_t step3, uchar* dst, size_t step,
2588 Size size)
2589{
2590 step1 /= sizeof(src1[0]);
2591 step2 /= sizeof(src2[0]);
2592 step3 /= sizeof(src3[0]);
2593
2594 for( ; size.height--; src1 += step1, src2 += step2, src3 += step3, dst += step )
2595 {
2596 int x = 0;
2597 #if CV_ENABLE_UNROLLED
2598 for( ; x <= size.width - 4; x += 4 )
2599 {
2600 int t0, t1;
2601 t0 = src2[x] <= src1[x] && src1[x] <= src3[x];
2602 t1 = src2[x+1] <= src1[x+1] && src1[x+1] <= src3[x+1];
2603 dst[x] = (uchar)-t0; dst[x+1] = (uchar)-t1;
2604 t0 = src2[x+2] <= src1[x+2] && src1[x+2] <= src3[x+2];
2605 t1 = src2[x+3] <= src1[x+3] && src1[x+3] <= src3[x+3];
2606 dst[x+2] = (uchar)-t0; dst[x+3] = (uchar)-t1;
2607 }
2608 #endif
2609 for( ; x < size.width; x++ )
2610 dst[x] = (uchar)-(src2[x] <= src1[x] && src1[x] <= src3[x]);
2611 }
2612}

2657static void inRangeReduce(const uchar* src, uchar* dst, size_t len, int cn)
2658{
2659 int k = cn % 4 ? cn % 4 : 4;
2660 size_t i, j;
2661 if( k == 1 )
2662 for( i = j = 0; i < len; i++, j += cn )
2663 dst[i] = src[j];
2664 else if( k == 2 )
2665 for( i = j = 0; i < len; i++, j += cn )
2666 dst[i] = src[j] & src[j+1];
2667 else if( k == 3 )
2668 for( i = j = 0; i < len; i++, j += cn )
2669 dst[i] = src[j] & src[j+1] & src[j+2];
2670 else
2671 for( i = j = 0; i < len; i++, j += cn )
2672 dst[i] = src[j] & src[j+1] & src[j+2] & src[j+3];
2673
2674 for( ; k < cn; k += 4 )
2675 {
2676 for( i = 0, j = k; i < len; i++, j += cn )
2677 dst[i] &= src[j] & src[j+1] & src[j+2] & src[j+3];
2678 }
2679}
2680
2681typedef void (*InRangeFunc)( const uchar* src1, size_t step1, const uchar* src2, size_t step2,
2682 const uchar* src3, size_t step3, uchar* dst, size_t step, Size sz );
2683
2684static InRangeFunc getInRangeFunc(int depth)
2685{
2686 static InRangeFunc inRangeTab[] =
2687 {
2688 (InRangeFunc)GET_OPTIMIZED(inRange8u), (InRangeFunc)GET_OPTIMIZED(inRange8s), (InRangeFunc)GET_OPTIMIZED(inRange16u),
2689 (InRangeFunc)GET_OPTIMIZED(inRange16s), (InRangeFunc)GET_OPTIMIZED(inRange32s), (InRangeFunc)GET_OPTIMIZED(inRange32f),
2690 (InRangeFunc)inRange64f, 0
2691 };
2692
2693 return inRangeTab[depth];
2694}
2695
2696}
2697
2698void cv::inRange(InputArray _src, InputArray _lowerb,
2699 InputArray _upperb, OutputArray _dst)
2700{
2701 int skind = _src.kind(), lkind = _lowerb.kind(), ukind = _upperb.kind();
2702 Mat src = _src.getMat(), lb = _lowerb.getMat(), ub = _upperb.getMat();
2703
2704 bool lbScalar = false, ubScalar = false;
2705
2706 if( (lkind == _InputArray::MATX && skind != _InputArray::MATX) ||
2707 src.size != lb.size || src.type() != lb.type() )
2708 {
2709 if( !checkScalar(lb, src.type(), lkind, skind) )
2710 CV_Error( CV_StsUnmatchedSizes,
2711 "The lower bounary is neither an array of the same size and same type as src, nor a scalar");
2712 lbScalar = true;
2713 }
2714
2715 if( (ukind == _InputArray::MATX && skind != _InputArray::MATX) ||
2716 src.size != ub.size || src.type() != ub.type() )
2717 {
2718 if( !checkScalar(ub, src.type(), ukind, skind) )
2719 CV_Error( CV_StsUnmatchedSizes,
2720 "The upper bounary is neither an array of the same size and same type as src, nor a scalar");
2721 ubScalar = true;
2722 }
2723
2724 CV_Assert( ((int)lbScalar ^ (int)ubScalar) == 0 );
2725
2726 int cn = src.channels(), depth = src.depth();
2727
2728 size_t esz = src.elemSize();
2729 size_t blocksize0 = (size_t)(BLOCK_SIZE + esz-1)/esz;
2730
2731 _dst.create(src.dims, src.size, CV_8U);
2732 Mat dst = _dst.getMat();
2733 InRangeFunc func = getInRangeFunc(depth);
2734
2735 const Mat* arrays_sc[] = { &src, &dst, 0 };
2736 const Mat* arrays_nosc[] = { &src, &dst, &lb, &ub, 0 };
2737 uchar* ptrs[4];
2738
2739 NAryMatIterator it(lbScalar && ubScalar ? arrays_sc : arrays_nosc, ptrs);
2740 size_t total = it.size, blocksize = std::min(total, blocksize0);
2741
2742 AutoBuffer<uchar> _buf(blocksize*(((int)lbScalar + (int)ubScalar)*esz + cn) + 2*cn*sizeof(int) + 128);
2743 uchar *buf = _buf, *mbuf = buf, *lbuf = 0, *ubuf = 0;
2744 buf = alignPtr(buf + blocksize*cn, 16);
2745
2746 if( lbScalar && ubScalar )
2747 {
2748 lbuf = buf;
2749 ubuf = buf = alignPtr(buf + blocksize*esz, 16);
2750
2751 CV_Assert( lb.type() == ub.type() );
2752 int scdepth = lb.depth();
2753
2754 if( scdepth != depth && depth < CV_32S )
2755 {
2756 int* ilbuf = (int*)alignPtr(buf + blocksize*esz, 16);
2757 int* iubuf = ilbuf + cn;
2758
2759 BinaryFunc sccvtfunc = getConvertFunc(scdepth, CV_32S);
2760 sccvtfunc(lb.data, 0, 0, 0, (uchar*)ilbuf, 0, Size(cn, 1), 0);
2761 sccvtfunc(ub.data, 0, 0, 0, (uchar*)iubuf, 0, Size(cn, 1), 0);
2762 int minval = cvRound(getMinVal(depth)), maxval = cvRound(getMaxVal(depth));
2763
2764 for( int k = 0; k < cn; k++ )
2765 {
2766 if( ilbuf[k] > iubuf[k] || ilbuf[k] > maxval || iubuf[k] < minval )
2767 ilbuf[k] = minval+1, iubuf[k] = minval;
2768 }
2769 lb = Mat(cn, 1, CV_32S, ilbuf);
2770 ub = Mat(cn, 1, CV_32S, iubuf);
2771 }
2772
2773 convertAndUnrollScalar( lb, src.type(), lbuf, blocksize );
2774 convertAndUnrollScalar( ub, src.type(), ubuf, blocksize );
2775 }
2776
2777 for( size_t i = 0; i < it.nplanes; i++, ++it )
2778 {
2779 for( size_t j = 0; j < total; j += blocksize )
2780 {
2781 int bsz = (int)MIN(total - j, blocksize);
2782 size_t delta = bsz*esz;
2783 uchar *lptr = lbuf, *uptr = ubuf;
2784 if( !lbScalar )
2785 {
2786 lptr = ptrs[2];
2787 ptrs[2] += delta;
2788 }
2789 if( !ubScalar )
2790 {
2791 int idx = !lbScalar ? 3 : 2;
2792 uptr = ptrs[idx];
2793 ptrs[idx] += delta;
2794 }
2795 func( ptrs[0], 0, lptr, 0, uptr, 0, cn == 1 ? ptrs[1] : mbuf, 0, Size(bsz*cn, 1));
2796 if( cn > 1 )
2797 inRangeReduce(mbuf, ptrs[1], bsz, cn);
2798 ptrs[0] += delta;
2799 ptrs[1] += bsz;
2800 }
2801 }
2802}
